            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "With https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/26564 merged, extmarks will no longer disappear in this repro. However all extmarks (not just diagnostics) inside the formatted region will be moved to the position just after the formatted region. This is caused by the splice operation in `nvim_buf_set_text()`:\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/320e9c1c21817fd76b84345018661f70437fa4b5/src/nvim/api/buffer.c#L448-L457\r\n\r\n    // Invalidate any which lie in the \r\n    // changed range, and move any in the remainder of the buffer.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure the invalidation part is correct. Maybe we can `mark_col_adjust()/extmark_splice()` for the added/removed text on a line, instead of invalidating the entire region. That would still make paired extmarks have 0 length(hiding highlight marks) but keep unpaired marks on the same line. This would also avoid the need for the workaround added in #14630.",
